{"content": "Medicare also covers inpatient respite care, which is care you get in a\nMedicare-approved facility so that your usual caregiver (family member or\nfriend) can rest. You can stay up to 5 days each time you get respite care.\nAfter 6 months, you can continue to get hospice care as long as the hospice\nmedical director or hospice doctor recertifies (at a face-to-face meeting) that\nyou\u2019re still terminally ill.\nYou pay:\n\u2022 Nothing for hospice care.\n", "content_type": "text", "score": null, "meta": {"_split_id": 143, "_split_overlap": [{"doc_id": "d30b71b2aa7fa5be5ebf27939e001752", "range": [0, 163]}, {"doc_id": "680d9d8b736283a91fb78a200f9ea19a", "range": [222, 443]}]}, "id_hash_keys": ["content"], "embedding": null, "id": "12ae24e8bccecde6f3e4afb623e6f540"}